{"article_id":"Q2irSJAbVvItD7fV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN ) -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"While President Barack Obama ' s attempts","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to increase the nation ' s minimum wage through legislation","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"have stalled in Congress ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"the White House announced plans on Tuesday","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"to use the president ' s executive powers","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"to partially address the problem .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Just hours before the President is scheduled to deliver his fifth State of the Union address ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"the White House revealed","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that Obama will issue an executive order","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"to increase the minimum wage for new federal contract workers .","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"The action will cover all workers","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"employed under future government contracts ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"ensuring that none is paid less than $ 10.10 an hour .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"In a fact sheet","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"announcing the action ,","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"the White House highlighted several occupations","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that will be helped by the move ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"including kitchen and laundry workers on military bases , as well as janitors at federal buildings and construction workers at government building sites .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"\" The President has embraced the idea in the past","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"that he can use his authority as President and the powers","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"available to the President","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"to advance his agenda on behalf of the American people , \"","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"White House Press Secretary Jay Carney said at his briefing on Monday .","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"\" What we have said is that he views 2014 as a year of action","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"and that he has tasked his team","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"to come up with new ways","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"in which we can","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"- he can -","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"advance that agenda . \"","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"An administration official confirmed","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"the action will only apply to new contracts ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"and the White House believes","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"contractors will have time","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"to factor the new wage requirements into future bids .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Included in Tuesday ' s announcement was a call","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"for Congress to pass an increase in the minimum wage nationwide","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"and an endorsement of a proposal","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"put forward by two senior Democrats , Sen. Tom Harkin of Iowa and Rep. George Miller of California .","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"The proposal would raise the minimum wage for all workers in stages ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"ultimately reaching $ 10.10 an hour ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"while also indexing the wage floor to inflation going forward .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"Tuesday morning , House Speaker John Boehner pushed back against the executive action by the President .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"`` This idea","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"that he 's just going to go it alone ,","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"I have to remind him","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"we do have a constitution .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"And the Congress writes the laws ,","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"and the President 's job is to execute the laws faithfully .","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"And","depth":13},{"id":50,"text":"if he tries to ignore this","depth":14},{"id":51,"text":"he 's going to run into a brick wall , ''","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"the top Republican in the House told reporters .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"`` Were just not going to sit here","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"and let the President trample all over us , ''","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"Boehner added .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"The White House says","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"the President has the authority","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"to make the move .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"Cecilia Muñoz , director of the White House Domestic Policy Council , said in an interview Tuesday with CNN Senior White House Correspondent Jim Acosta","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"that the President `` clearly has the authority ''","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"to raise the minimum wage for federal contract workers .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"Obama has made wages and economic inequality a central theme of his second term in office ,","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"raising the issue repeatedly ,","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"including during a call for an extension of emergency unemployment benefits in his first public event of 2014 .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"\" America is getting stronger ,","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"and we 've made progress , \"","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"the President said .","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"\" And the economy is growing ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"and we 've got to do more","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"to make sure","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"that all Americans share in that growth .","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"We 've got to help our businesses create more jobs .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"We 've got to make sure","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"those jobs offer the wages and benefits","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"that let families rebuild a little security .","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"In other words , we 've got to make sure","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"that this recovery leaves nobody behind .","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"And we 've got a lot of work to do on that front . \"","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"Two national polls","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"conducted in the past two weeks","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"both indicate widespread support","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"for raising the minimum wage to $ 10.10 an hour .","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"Seventy-two percent of those","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"questioned in a CBS News survey","depth":7},{"id":85,"text":"and 73 % of those","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"questioned in a Pew Research Center poll","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"they favor the move .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"Both surveys indicated a partisan divide ,","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"with around nine in ten Democrats and seven in ten independents in support","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"of raising the minimum wage to $ 10.10 an hour , and Republicans divided .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":183,"left":0,"right":182,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":182,"left":152,"right":181,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":125,"right":151,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":97,"right":124,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":94,"right":96,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":94,"left":93,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":93,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":4,"right":95,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":124,"left":108,"right":123,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":108,"left":103,"right":107,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":100,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":7,"right":99,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":99,"left":8,"right":98,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":101,"right":13,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"lef